race.comment: NEW ROMANCE (8) is right up to this at best and was heading in the right direction before folding up badly at Yarra Valley. She will position forward from a handy gate and deserves another chance. MR RIBTICKLER (4) was quickly back on track placing at Camperdown over a mile. Has a wide gate but will cross over and may be the one to control the race. On a 7-day return and must be pleasing. CLISTE (7) ran a competitive number placing distantly over a mile at Stawell. Peaks for this and the inside gate should advantage. CONALTRI (1) backs up quickly and holds each-way claims on best figures. Keeping safe.
